    "category": "Operational Playbook",
    "content": "return ( ); \"use client\"; interface PlaybookPageLayoutProps children: ReactNode; : PlaybookPageLayoutProps) return ( /* Content */ children /* Footer */ ); \"use client\"; [ key: \"full-matrix\", label: \"Full Matrix\", title: \"Decision Rights Matrix\", description: \"What each role can decide independently vs. what needs Founder approval\", content: , , key: \"by-role\", label: \"By Role\", title: \"Decision Rights by Role\", description: \"Quick reference: What each role can decide alone\", content: , , key: \"founder-approval\", label: \"Founder Approval\", title: \"Decisions Requiring Founder Approval\", description: \"These items ALWAYS need Founder approval - everything else is delegated\", content: , , key: \"quick-reference\", label: \"Quick Reference\", title: \"Quick Reference: Key Thresholds\", description: \"Print this page for easy reference\", content: , , ]; return ( Operations Playbook Decision Rights Defining who can make what decisions without Founder approval to enable maximum delegation. Purpose This document defines WHO can make WHAT decisions WITHOUT Founder approval. The goal is MAXIMUM DELEGATION : Team members should be able to make most decisions independently Founder approval is only required for high-impact/high-risk decisions When in doubt, refer to the thresholds defined here How to Use Find the decision category (Financial, Client, HR, etc.) Check if your decision falls within &quot;Can Decide Alone&quot; limits If YES → Make the decision, inform relevant parties If NO → Escalate to Founder with recommendation Decision Authority Levels Escalation Rule When escalating to Founder, ALWAYS include: The issue/decision needed What you&apos;ve already reviewed or tried Your recommended action Deadline for decision (if time-sensitive) The Founder should never receive an escalation without a recommendation. ); authority delegation approval founder levels escalation permissions decisions authorize who can responsibility accountability sign off approve"
