    "name": "Hiring Pipeline SOP",
    "href": "/playbook/hiring-sop",
    "category": "Operational Playbook",
    "content": "return ( ); \"use client\"; interface PlaybookPageLayoutProps children: ReactNode; : PlaybookPageLayoutProps) return ( /* Content */ children /* Footer */ ); // ✅ Server Component by default return ( /* Header Block */ Operations Playbook Hiring Pipeline SOP Standard Operating Procedure for Recruiting & Hiring Purpose Ensure consistent, efficient hiring that fills roles quickly with quality candidates while providing a professional candidate experience. 1 . Hiring Pipeline Stages # Stage What Happens Owner Timeline 1 Job Posting Create JD, post to job boards, share in networks HR Coordinator Day 1 2 Application Review Screen resumes, filter qualified candidates HR Coordinator Within 24hrs 3 Initial Screening 15-min phone/video call, basic fit check HR Coordinator Day 2 4 Skills Assessment Role-specific test or task (1-2 hrs) HR + Ops Days 2-3 5 Ops Interview 30-45 min interview with Ops Coordinator Ops Coordinator Days 3-4 6 Founder Interview 30 min final interview, culture fit Founder Days 4-5 7 Reference Check Contact 2 references HR Coordinator Days 5-6 8 Offer & Contract Extend offer, negotiate, send contract Founder + HR Day 7 Target: Job posting to signed contract in 7 business days 2 . Role Responsibilities HR Coordinator Create and post job descriptions Screen all applications within 48 hours Conduct initial screening calls Coordinate interview scheduling Send skills assessments Conduct reference checks Prepare offer letters and contracts Send rejection emails to unsuccessful candidates Maintain hiring tracker and provide weekly report Ops Coordinator Define role requirements and success criteria Review skills assessment results Conduct Ops interview Complete interview scorecard Provide hire/no-hire recommendation Founder Approve job posting before publishing Conduct final culture-fit interview Make final hiring decision Approve compensation package 3 . Weekly Hiring Report Due: Every Friday by 10:00 PM | Submitted to: Founder Report must include: Section Details Open Positions List of all active job postings with days open Pipeline Summary # of candidates at each stage per role This Week&apos;s Activity Applications received, screenings done, interviews conducted Top Candidates Names and status of candidates in Stage 5+ Blockers / Needs Any issues slowing hiring, decisions needed from Founder Next Week Plan Planned interviews, expected offers, next actions 4 . Job Posting Channels OnlineJobs.ph — Primary for PH-based roles LinkedIn — For senior/specialized roles Facebook Groups — VA and freelancer communities Referrals — Team referral bonus program 5 . Candidate Communication SLAs Action Timeline Acknowledge application Within 24 hours (auto-reply OK) Schedule screening after resume review Within 24 hours of application Send rejection to non-qualified Within 2 business days of application Post-interview feedback Within 24 hours of interview Extend offer to selected candidate Same day as final decision ); recruiting hiring interview candidates screening offer contract sop job application applicant employment new hire recruitment resume cv"
