    "content": "\"use client\"; return ( ); return ( Operations Playbook PM Tool Standard Lark Tasks configuration and usage guidelines for project management /* Lark Tasks - Kanban Board Rules */ Lark Tasks - Kanban Board Rules ONE WORKSPACE ALL CLIENTS KANBAN VIEW WEEKLY ORGANIZATION /* What It Looks Like */ What It Looks Like ↑ Lark Tasks with Group by: Client • Week sections show project progress /* 1. Workspace Structure */ Workspace Structure Element Rule Workspace ONE workspace for all client work View Kanban board Custom Field Create &quot;Client&quot; field (e.g., XBathrooms, ABC Coaching) Group By Group by: Client (each column = 1 client) Week Field Create &quot;Week&quot; field: Week 1, Week 2, Week 3, Week 4, Week 5, Go-Live, Retainer Sort By Sort by: Week (tasks appear in week order within each client) /* 2. Task Naming Convention */ Task Naming Convention Format: [CLIENT] Task Name Client Abbreviation Examples Client Name Abbreviation Example Task XBathrooms [XB] [XB] Homepage - Build ABC Coaching [ABC] [ABC] Email Sequence - Draft Sunrise Dental [SD] [SD] Workflow - Appointment Reminder Abbreviation Rule: \" \" First letters of each word (2-3 letters). If already taken, add number. /* 3. Task Requirements */ Task Requirements Every task MUST have: Client prefix [XB], [ABC], etc. Owner One person assigned (not multiple) Due date End of the week it&apos;s assigned to Column/Week Placed in correct weekly column ); \"use client\"; interface PlaybookPageLayoutProps children: ReactNode; : PlaybookPageLayoutProps) return ( /* Content */ children /* Footer */ ); lark tasks kanban project management task naming workspace tool software board columns status tracking assignment lists due dates owners"
